olive oil
40 g butter
2 tbs milk
¼ tsp salt
¼ tsp pepper
2 Potato
½ head Broccoli
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Diced Chicken
½ packet Cream
1 packet Dijon Mustard

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a large saucepan with boiling water, then add a
generous pinch of salt.
• Peel potato and cut into large chunks.
• Cook potato in the boiling water over high heat until easily pierced with a
fork, 12-15 minutes. Drain and return to the pan.
• Add the butter and milk to potato and season generously with salt. Mash
until smooth. Cover to keep warm.

• Meanwhile, cut broccoli (see ingredients) into small florets, then roughly
chop stalk.
• Add broccoli and a splash of water to a microwave-safe bowl, then cover
with a damp paper towel.
• Microwave broccoli on high until just tender, 2-4 minutes.
• Drain broccoli, then return to the bowl. Add baby leaves, season, drizzle
with olive oil and toss to combine. Cover to keep warm.

• While veggies are steaming, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large frying pan
over high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and
cooked through, 5-6 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium. Stir in cream (see ingredients), Dijon mustard,
the salt and pepper, tossing chicken to coat, 1 minute.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it is no longer pink inside.

• Divide mash, steamed greens and creamy mustard chicken between plates.
• Spoon over any remaining sauce from pan to serve. Enjoy!

ELEVATE ME: If you've added extra ingredients to your meal, sprinkle over
Parmesan cheese and flaked almonds. Cut lemon into wedges, add a generous
squeeze of lemon juice and serve with any remaining wedges.